    • getForeignColumns

      public Expression<?> getForeignColumns()
      Specified by:
      getForeignColumns in interface EntityColumn<E extends Entity>
      Returns:
      the foreign columns to be used to display the foreign object, or null if the original expression is just a value. These columns are generally those defined in the domain class, but it's possible to override them when the column is parsed from json using the "foreignColumns" key. Ex: {expression: 'myEntity', foreignColumns: '[icon,name]'}

    • getForeignWhere

      public String getForeignWhere()
      Specified by:
      getForeignWhere in interface EntityColumn<E extends Entity>
      Returns:
      the foreign condition to be used when selecting a new foreign object, or null if the original expression is just a value. This condition is generally the one defined in the foreign field, but it's possible to override it when the column is parsed from json using the "foreignCondition" key. Ex: {expression: 'myEntity', foreignWhere: '!cancelled'}

    • getForeignSearchCondition

      public String getForeignSearchCondition()
      Specified by:
      getForeignSearchCondition in interface EntityColumn<E extends Entity>
      Returns:
      the foreign search condition to be used when selecting a new foreign object, or null if the original expression is just a value. This search condition is generally the one defined in the domain class, but it's possible to override it when the column is parsed from json using the "foreignFields" key. Ex: {expression: 'myEntity', foreignSearchCondition: 'name like ?searchLike'}

    • getDisplayExpression

      public Expression<E> getDisplayExpression()
      Specified by:
      getDisplayExpression in interface EntityColumn<E extends Entity>
      Returns:
      the expression to be used to evaluate all values of the display result set for that column. It is the same original expression if it expresses just a value but if it expresses a foreign object, the foreign fields declared in the foreign class to display such an entity will be used instead.
